    <title>COLOUR / COLOR Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">COLOUR<sp/>integer-expression</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Sets the <bold>text foreground colour</bold> to a VGA palette entry (0â€“15). <linebreak/>
 The default terminal colour is <bold>7</bold> (white).</para>
<para><image type="html" name="colours.png"></image>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Both British and American spellings are accepted: <computeroutput>COLOUR</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>COLOR</computeroutput>.</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="COLOUR_1example-6_1s1"><sect2 id="COLOUR_1example-6_1s2"><sect3 id="COLOUR_1example-6_1s3"><sect4 id="COLOUR_1example-6_1s4"><sect5 id="COLOUR_1example-6">
<title>Example</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">COLOUR<sp/>14</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;This<sp/>text<sp/>is<sp/>bright<sp/>yellow.&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect5></sect4></sect3></sect2></sect1>
